{"key":"processedPost-16096328","value":{"id":16096328,"first":16095491,"last":16097967,"when":1334572692,"utime":"04/16/12 01:38 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>iwannabemro said:</b><br />I'm no pro, but I'll share my problems to help. I live in the desert never higher than 30% humidity here. My agar petri dishes dry up&nbsp; in 7-10 days. So both times I've tried I'd get to the 3rd or 4th transfer and forget to transfer and loose my progress.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />You're supposed to wrap the dishes with parafilm and then place each dish in a ziplock bag.&nbsp; I keep them this way for several months, and it's rarely over 10% humidity here.<br /><br />To isolate strains, you simply make a swipe of spores on agar, and then as the various strains(sectors) emerge, you transfer each one to its own dish.&nbsp; Use these to inoculate cakes or other substrates, and when you find the one you want to keep, go back to the original culture and grow it from then on.&nbsp; Easy. <br /><a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Strain-Isolation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Strain isolation on agar.</a><br />RR","title":"Re: Isolating for potency","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}